    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      MultipleQueueDispatcher()
      Creates a MultipleQueueDispatcher that will service events from a queue until it is empty and then moves on to the next queue.
      MultipleQueueDispatcher(int queueServiceMax)
      Creates a MultipleQueueDispatcher that will service up to queueServiceMax events from a queue before then moves on to the next queue One thread will service all events
      MultipleQueueDispatcher(int queueServiceMax, int maxThreads)
      Creates a MultipleQueueDispatcher that will service up to queueServiceMax events from a queue before then moves on to the next queue Up to maxThreads will be used to service events
